node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

Dreamy seaside hangouts with @meganhassa via @lifewithelliott. 🌴 Swaying palm trees, vibrant blue skies, and calm waters—what more could you ask for? 😍

Known as one of the most strikingly scenic islands in French Polynesia, Moorea is a true gem that's loved by couples, families, and locals. The island possesses jagged mountains, sandy beaches, and a relaxed vibe that makes you never want to leave. 🇵🇫

When was your last beach trip? Are you thinking of traveling to French Polynesia anytime soon? 💭

📽 @lifewithelliott
💃 @meganhassa
📍 Moorea, French Polynesia
🎶 October Eyes - Alt Bloom

The art of incense making via @_pifou. ❤️ When in Vietnam, an unmissable experience would be to visit a traditional incense craft village to find out how incense sticks are made. 🇻🇳

The use of incense has a special significance in many Asian countries, including Vietnam. As a way to commemorate important occasions and celebrations, Vietnamese people have burned incense for centuries. Burning incense is also a way of praying for and remembering ancestors. 🕯

Do you enjoy immersing in cultural activities during your travels? What are some of your most eye-opening experiences?

📽 @_pifou
📍 Quang Phu Cau, Vietnam
🎶 Scent of Lotus Petals - Asian Music Sanctuary

Living the dream with @gossegoss and @roamingpuppers in Geiranger, one of the most beautiful destinations in Norway that brims with pristine natural landscapes. 😍🐕

"We ended up having Skageflå—which is one of the most popular hikes—all to ourselves. Videos and pictures will never do this place justice though, and it is popular for a reason! I just can’t believe how lucky we got. 🍃"

If you're looking for a sign to explore the mountains (with your furry friend), this is it! Would you consider a nature-filled getaway in Norway? 🇳🇴

📽 @gossegoss
🐶 @roamingpuppers
📍 Skageflå, Geiranger, Norway
🎶 What A Wonderful World - Louis Armstrong

That magical bioluminescent glow via @jordan_robins, an unforgettable and captivating sight you'll be lucky to witness at Jervis Bay in Australia. 🇦🇺

Notoriously difficult to capture in photographs and videos, bioluminescence can only be spotted at a few locations around the world. In Jervis Bay, the best time to catch sight of this natural wonder varies but is usually seen between the months of May and August. 💙

Is seeing this in real life part of your bucket list? Or are you one of the lucky few who have already seen this? 🤩

📸 @jordan_robins
📍 Jervis Bay, Australia

Do you dream of exploring Southern Italy? What makes you want to travel here? 💭

Marveling at the foggy views with @pilotviking and @fenris_the_vikingdog by Lysefjorden, Norway. Spot the fluffy wagging tail of Fenris, who's enjoying the view and company! 🖤

Located in the Ryfylke area in southwestern Norway, Lysefjorden is a vast 42​-kilometer fjord. Its area is particularly well-known for the Preikestolen cliff, which overlooks the fjord and offers an incredible vantage point over the dramatic landscape. 🇳🇴

Do you go on trips with your furry best friends, and if yes, where was your last adventure together?

📽 @pilotviking
🐺 @fenris_the_vikingdog
📍 Lysefjorden, Norway

Van life daydreams via @75vibes_. 🌞 Whenever you're feeling stuck in a rut, remember that there are so many beautiful places out there you have yet to see. 🚐

This was shot in the Daintree Rainforest near Cape Tribulation in Queensland, Australia. The rainforest is one of the most biologically diverse rainforests in the world, being home to a large percentage of Australia's animal population. The area also offers a handful of stunning beaches with dazzling sunshine and crystal clear calm water. 🌴

Have you explored Queensland yet? What are your favorite road trip destinations in Australia? 🇦🇺
